@node "autor"

   Don't you know this situation ? Having trouble with your modem getting a
   proper connection ? How were these bloody commands ? Which bloody register ?
   Where the hell ist the manual ? Which page ?
   Well, I had it too often and now I can find what I need online.
   I found the text in a mailbox @{"Dino-Box, Cologne" link "dino"} and made it
   accessible via AmigaGuide.
   So thanks must go to @{"ZyXEL Communications Corp." link "manufacturer"} for
   their great modem series and to Commodore-Amiga, Inc. for making AmigaGuide
   publicly available.

   I can be reached at

   Christoph Guelicher
   Dohlenweg 4                    Universitaet Siegen, FTS
   D-57078 Siegen                 D-57068 Siegen

   CG@winfcg.swb.de               CG@hrz.uni-siegen.d400.de

@endnode

